picoctf WinAntiDbg0x100 writeup

1.use x32-dbg to open it 

2.and we can see it uses <IsDebuggerPresent> to know whether we use debugger

3.we have two options , first is changing its return value , second is changing its jump command

first => 
set breakpoint at "call dword ptr ds:[<IsDebuggerPresent>]"
run it
go to next command 
change eax's value to 0
run it

second =>
set breakpoint at "call dword ptr ds:[<IsDebuggerPresent>]"
run it
press "je winantidbg0x100.31161B"
press space 
change "jz 0x0031161B" to "jmp 0x0031161B"
run it

4.look its log 

5.get flag!
